# Interview Definitions

### Token Bucket

A rate limiting algorithm where tokens are generated at a fixed rate, and each request consumes one token. Requests are accepted only if tokens are available.

### Leaky Bucket

A queue-based algorithm where requests are processed at a constant rate. Excess requests are discarded when the queue becomes full.

### Fixed Window

Counts requests within fixed time intervals and resets the counter at the beginning of every new interval.

### Sliding Window Log

Stores timestamps for every request and checks the number of requests within a moving time window.

### Sliding Window Counter

Uses counters from the current and previous windows to estimate the number of requests, reducing memory usage while maintaining high accuracy.
